</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ubraksus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>braksus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://us.f1.yahoofs.com/users/29067159/bc/My+Photos/Braksus%27s+new+icon.jpg?bciuVh8AOTobQ49x" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(1/22/02 8:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on crowd control</span><hr size=1> mez all pops, then let the tank decide which one to attack first.  nobody should attack ANYTHING until the tank does.  make your group learn that they have to take a few hits while you get things under control.  fighting back before the group is ready just makes things worse.  or, if your group wasn't fighting anything when you got the adds, use a nice stunlock to give the tank a few seconds to select a target, then mez the others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uladihawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ladihawk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(1/22/02 3:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on crowd control</span><hr size=1> Thanks i never even thought about that. I will give that a try tonight in HHK. <p><br><p align="left"><img
