51st Illusionist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uelazeel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elazeel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(2/7/02 12:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on crowd control</span><hr size=1> Another thing that I have found to work well:<br>
<br>
Have everyone set their assist key to simply /assist rather than /assist MT_01 (or %T)  this way, they can hotkey target the MT, then hit the assist key 3 times to be sure the mob they are on is aggroed on the MT.  What they will see is their target go from MT to mob to MT, back to mob on the 3rd hit.  You may have to teach a few people how to hotkey target (f1-f8, depending on settings), but you will help yourself and others in the long run.  It does fail occasionally, but usually due to the MT changing his mind after targeting.<br>
<br>
HHK was actually very good for me as a CC tutorial, but then I had decided by that point that if a group got me killed more than once per hour, I was not in the right group, lol.<br>
<br>
